[32m+[m[32m# Contributing to VXNeo[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThank you for your interest in contributing to VXNeo! 🎉[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Development Setup[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Fork and clone**[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m   git clone https://github.com/jas77409/vxneo.git[m
[32m+[m[32m   cd vxneo[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Install dependencies**[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m   npm install[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Configure environment**[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m   cp .env.example .env[m
[32m+[m[32m   # Edit .env with your Supabase credentials[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Start development server**[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m   npm run dev[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Pull Request Process[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature`[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Make your changes[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Test thoroughly[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Commit with clear messages: `git commit -m "feat: add amazing feature"`[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Push to your fork: `git push origin feature/amazing-feature`[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Open a Pull Request[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Code Style[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use Prettier for formatting[m
[32m+[m[32m- Follow ESLint rules[m
[32m+[m[32m- Write meaningful commit messages (conventional commits)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Add comments for complex logic[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Commit Message Format[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m<type>: <subject>[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m<body>[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTypes:[m
[32m+[m[32m- `feat`: New feature[m
[32m+[m[32m- `fix`: Bug fix[m
[32m+[m[32m- `docs`: Documentation[m
[32m+[m[32m- `style`: Formatting[m
[32m+[m[32m- `refactor`: Code restructuring[m
[32m+[m[32m- `test`: Adding tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- `chore`: Maintenance[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Testing[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mnpm test[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Reporting Issues[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUse GitHub Issues with:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Clear description[m
[32m+[m[32m- Steps to reproduce[m
[32m+[m[32m- Expected vs actual behavior[m
[32m+[m[32m- Environment details (OS, Node version, etc.)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Security[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReport security vulnerabilities privately to: contact@vxneo.com[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Do not create public issues for security vulnerabilities.**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Questions?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFeel free to open a discussion or reach out![m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThank you for contributing! 🙏[m
